I"‰<h1 id="intro-to-information-theory">Intro to Information Theory</h1>

<p>Rather than asking about what is the information, it is more about what happens to the information.</p>

<p>Information in the context of communication (includes information storage)</p>

<p>A theory of information transmission.</p>

<p>The meaning of the information is not considered.</p>

<p>PAPER TO READ: A Mathematical theory of Communication. (1948, Claude Shannon)</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Definition (Information Theory): Information theory is the study of the fundamental limits and potential of the representation and transmission of information.</p>
</blockquote>

